You get a range of grimm for each dance battle. The amount is higher for later battles, and you get more for hard lessons than normal lessons. Events give you only 300, but you get higher experience. Need more grimm? Revisit hard battles you know you can win without glowsticks.
Keep an eye on other rewards in your to-do. There are some tasks you can complete on purpose to get rewards you need!

Why did I forget to link the wiki?
https://t.co/fD4okQzhl1
Special events will give you AP, both as rewards and gifts in the mail (when the event is released.) You can save this for later, but check the expiration dates!
If you play an event that has story keys, whether it's the first time or in a Lonely Devil tour, the keys get converted to grimm after the event ends.

Pop quiz events give you extra points for each battle if you've pulled "cheat cards" from nightmare or combined reward card pieces or leveled up cheat cards. Get as far as you can, because when they come back in 6 months as Lonely Devil, all you get is 120 points.

"Missions" in a birthday event might not all look worthwhile, but completing them all gets you a card.

If you don't think you can get enough pieces in the rewards to complete a card, it will sit in your card pieces collection forever. You can not collect them if you don't want.

You can do normal battles as much as you want, but you're limited to 3x for each hard or event battle. D-energy or 5 DP will get you 3 more of that battle when you click the + next to battles left, but you also get 1 more each time you click this and watch an ad. https://t.co/jUnCi1QL46

Always collect your free AP! 20 from special guests, 60 (or 120 VIP) from fridge mission, 20 from daily rewards, and 50 from watching ads.

Click this button. You can mute the ads, get yourself more coffee, whatever, and you'll still get your 10AP. https://t.co/aiR3B1rmdW

...like zombie, scarecrow, berserker, frog, and even confuse because they lower your battle points rather than stop them. So give it a shot before you blow glowsticks on them. AP is cheaper than glowsticks.

Also, don't be too intimidated by Mr. Smiley. You can get one star in a battle with as many as 70k lower strength than your opponent if they don't have attacks like sleep, paralyze, or stun. You might still have a chance against the attacks that transform...

Don't worry about getting 3 stars every time. Just unlock the battles. That way you can continue the story and access special items for devil's tree. You can go back later and get the extra stars and unlock extra lessons.

That being said, if the card's not strong enough or your opponents skills will knock you out so you can't tap all three of your characters at once, it doesn't matter. Pick another card that can counter the attack or refresh your team instead.

Don't purchase items you can get from jobs!

The reason you want three cards of each sin is that matching the big flashing sin next to the task number gives you a 2.6x bonus to that card's score, and matching the small flashing sin gives you a 1.3x bonus.

...summoning sale for demon vouchers (150 DP for 10) and devil's tree spaces for story keys.

You can also get DV, story keys, and glowsticks with raven.

You get raven by working ristorante six (work the other jobs to unlock it), upping skills by pulling cards, events & guests.

...glowsticks for 20 DP after you lose a battle.

You get grimm/AP/glowsticks/story keys/demon vouchers for 99 DP every 5 levels until you hit 100, then every level after. Good deal if you need ALL those things.

Otherwise, use the cheaper sales for AP/glowsticks...

Flash sales are good, but they will suck up your devil points. You can get them twice a day, 12 hours apart. If you get the message for a flash sale and decline it, you can't get it for another 12 hours.

200AP for 10 DP when you run out of AP, or 5,000 grimm/50 AP/5 rainbow...

You can also get AP from "friends." Just add them. It's not real friends, nothing else happens but giving each other AP. As you level up, you can have up to 100 friends and get a max of 50 AP from them per day.
Every day when the game resets, you can get gifts from surprise guests after winning a battle and having all heart interactions. You can get 1 raven twice, 1,000 grimm twice, and 10 AP twice.

...remember that when you get new URs or SSRs, they're going to need those watches and mugs, too.

Level up your memory cards. Especially the ones that refresh your team. 

Refresh is a great ability when your cards can't counter your opponents' attacks.

SSRs are NOT useless. You'll get an SSR that counters sleep or berserker or counters with an attack WAY before you get a UR that does the same.

Leveling up N cards is a good way to get demon rewards or story keys for Devilgrams, but don't go nuts...

If you edit your teams so you have one for each sin, you have a better picture of which attributes you need more cards for, and which cards you want to level up or discard from the team when a better card arrives.

Surprise guests might be annoying, but increasing intimacy by interacting with them gets you phone calls ever five levels.

Quick clear is ok, but you don't get intimacy points or experience for your cards.

Don't save AP. You get 12 AP for free every hour that you're below max.

Things I wish I'd known when I started playing #ObeyMe...

There's a wiki with a ton of information.

You don't have to give presents to surprise guests to get big hearts. (The wiki tells you the interactions.)

You can swipe hearts and stars in battles.
